sections.text:
To describe the simulation programs we use a very simplified object oriented style language, where statements have the following form:
Subject.Predicate(Object);
where each identified triplet corresponds to a statement such as this. A simulation program is a statement list that only contains a given number or less statements. In addition, we write it into an image because it would be difficult to handle the statement list as a textual list of statements as it is shown in Fig. 1(c) where the input of the Q-learning is already an image. And finally, it may be noted that the sequence of such ”mental” images can be interpreted as visual imagination of Samu. Fig. 3 shows a sample mental image.
